        <Parent_String>photographers [300025687], artists by medium or work type [300386777], artists (visual artists) [300025103], people in the visual arts [300025101], people in the visual arts and related occupations [300239109], people in the arts [300168455], people in the arts and related occupations [300168331], people in the humanities [300025485], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Persons who oversee all the aspects of photography in a television, video, or filmmaking project, especially the lighting; they are particularly charged with achieving the photographic images and effects desired by the director. For operators of motion picture, video, or television cameras, use "cameramen."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personas que supervisan todos los aspectos de fotografía en un proyecto de televisión, video o producción cinematográfica, especialmente la iluminación; ellos están particularmente a cargo con el archivo de imágenes fotográficas y efectos deseados por el director. Para operadores de cámaras de cine, video o televisión, use "operador".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen die toezicht houden op alle fotografische aspecten in een televisie- of filmproject, met name de belichting. Ze zijn in het bijzonder belast met het bereiken van fotografische beelden en effecten die door de regisseur worden verlangd. Gebruik 'cameramensen' voor bedieners van film- of televisiecamera's.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>負責監督電視、錄影影像或電影製片圖像的人員(特別在燈光效果方面)。這些人員須負責達到導演所要求的攝影品質及效果。若為操作電影或電視拍攝用攝影機的從業人員，則稱之為「攝影師」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
